Package: scMetaboFlux
Title: Single-Cell Energy Metabolism Inference Engine
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2024-01-15
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Metabolic", family = "Analysis Team", 
           email = "dev@scmetaboFlux.org", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")))
Maintainer: Metabolic Analysis Team <dev@scmetaboFlux.org>
Author: Metabolic Analysis Team [aut, cre]
Description: Inferring cellular energy states from single-cell transcriptomics 
    via metabolic flux approximation. Converts transcriptomics data into quantitative 
    metabolic flux estimates including ATP production, glycolysis, OXPHOS activity,
    and metabolic phenotype classification at single-cell resolution.
    Key features include:
    (1) Pre-built metabolic gene sets for 12 pathways (KEGG/Reactome curated);
    (2) Multiple pathway scoring methods (AUCell, GSVA, mean expression);
    (3) Novel ATP production estimation algorithm;
    (4) Pseudo-flux calculation with rate-limiting enzyme weighting;
    (5) Classification of cells into 5 metabolic phenotypes;
    (6) Comprehensive visualization and differential analysis tools;
    (7) High-performance parallel processing for large datasets.
